parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat control can cause the seat to move independently while driving, which can lead to driver distraction, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver's seat moves forward or backward on its own
the seat control becomes fractured
the plastic covering of the electronic driver's seat adjuster detaches
the seat control motor
wires
and clip become exposed and loose
the seat cannot be adjusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on and stays on
a "ding" or "ring" sound is heard while driving
the airbag light comes on and stays on even after other lights go out
the airbag fails to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
loud noise from the steering column
power steering failure
increased effort required to steer the vehicle
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, leading to potential injury or death, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Burning smell
black smoke rolling out from under the hood
flames coming from under the engine
dash lights all lit up and flashing
sparks shooting out of the negative cable end
headlights flickering
fog lights burning out
and electrical components melting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Loud growling noise
especially when turning the steering wheel on interstate clover leaf exit/entrance ramps.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Lower Control Arm Bushing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front lower control arm bushings can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Failure of the front lower control arm bushings
reported by a dealer repair technician
requiring replacement of the entire control arm.
